<preface id="idg-osoperator-about-c-about-xml-1">
 <title>About this Manual</title>
 <para>
  This manual describes how system operators can monitor their OpenStack
  platforms with FUJITSU ServerView <phrase>Cloud Monitoring Manager</phrase> -
  hereafter referred to as <phrase>Cloud Monitoring Manager</phrase>
  (<phrase>CMM</phrase>).
 </para>
 <para>
  The manual is structured as follows:
 </para>
 <para>
  <informaltable colsep="1" frame="all" rowsep="1">
   <tgroup cols="2">
    <colspec colname="col2" colnum="1" colwidth="2.61*"/>
    <colspec colname="col3" colnum="2" colwidth="3.39*"/>
    <thead>
     <row>
      <entry colname="col2">Chapter</entry>
      <entry colname="col3">Description</entry>
     </row>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
     <row>
      <entry colname="col2"><xref linkend="idg-shared-intro-c-intro-xml-1"/>
      </entry>
      <entry colname="col3">Introduces <phrase>CMM</phrase> and the basic usage scenario of monitoring an OpenStack platform.</entry>
     </row>
     <row>
      <entry colname="col2"><xref linkend="idg-osoperator-install-c-osoinstall-xml-1"/>
      </entry>
      <entry colname="col3">Describes how to install the <phrase>CMM</phrase> components required for monitoring an OpenStack platform. </entry>
     </row>
     <row>
      <entry colname="col2"><xref linkend="idg-osoperator-prepare-c-osopreparetu-xml-1"/>
      </entry>
      <entry colname="col3">Describes how to prepare the monitoring environment for application operators. </entry>
     </row>
     <row>
      <entry colname="col2"><xref linkend="idg-shared-monitor-c-monitor-xml-1"/>
      </entry>
      <entry colname="col3">Describes the basic tasks involved in monitoring the OpenStack services and servers.</entry>
     </row>
     <row>
      <entry colname="col2"><xref linkend="idg-shared-logging-c-osologging-xml-1"/>
      </entry>
      <entry colname="col3">Describes the basic tasks involved in managing the log data from the OpenStack services and servers.</entry>
     </row>
